Package Library

Class Date

java.lang.Object
Library.Date
public class Date
extends java.lang.Object
Date class represents String of date object. Stores Year, Month, and Day of objects to compare.
Author:
Connie Chen, Tiffany Lee

    • isValid

      public boolean isValid()
      Checks if a Date object has a valid date. A valid date has the year after 1900 and does not surpass current date. Leap year and valid days of a month is checked also.
      Returns:
      true if the date is valid and false otherwise

      Parameters:

      name1 - of the first book to be compared
      name2 - of the second book to be compared
      Returns:
      true if the current Date instance is earlier than Date object passed in, false otherwise
